lyrics:
[Verse]
Leaving Belfast town, with hope in my heart
Joined the 36th Ulster, ready to depart
Bound for France and Flanders, to fight side by side
Little did we know, what awaited us inside

[Chorus]
Oh, the Battle of the Somme, it tore us apart
Brothers in arms, forever in my heart
The fields turned to crimson, as the cannons roared
We lost so many, at that dreadful war
